com.bluegosling.concurrent

Class ReadOnlyCompletableFuture<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.concurrent.CompletableFuture<T>
      • com.bluegosling.concurrent.InterruptibleCompletableFuture<T>
        • com.bluegosling.concurrent.ReadOnlyCompletableFuture<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the future value
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    CompletionStageFuture<T>, CompletionStage<T>, Future<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    RunnableReadOnlyCompletableFuture

    public class ReadOnlyCompletableFuture<T>
extends InterruptibleCompletableFuture<T>
    A completable future whose public API is read-only. Attempts to complete or obtrude a value or cause of failure will result in UnsupportedOperationExceptions. Also, calls toCompletableFuture() will clone the future, returning a new CompletableFuture that is kept in sync with the original, completing or failing with the same result or cause.

    In order for the future to be completed, this class provides protected API. This means that this class must be sub-classed to be useful. See RunnableReadOnlyCompletableFuture for an example.

    • Method Detail

      • setValue

        protected boolean setValue(T value)
        Completes the future with the given value. This is like complete(Object) except that it is intentionally protected, not public, so as to be used by sub-classes and preserving the read-only nature of the public API.
        Parameters:
        value - the result value
        Returns:
        true if the future is completed with the given value or false if the future was already completed (successfully, exceptionally, or from cancellation)

      • setFailure

        protected boolean setFailure(Throwable cause)
        Marks the future as failed due to the given cause. This is like completeExceptionally(Throwable) except that it is intentionally protected, not public, so as to be used by sub-classes and preserving the read-only nature of the public API.
        Parameters:
        cause - the cause of failure
        Returns:
        true if the future is completed with the given exception or false if the future was already completed (successfully, exceptionally, or from cancellation)

      • toCompletableFuture

        public CompletableFuture<T> toCompletableFuture()
        Returns a new CompletableFuture that completes with the same value or cause of failure as this future. The returned future is a standard future, not a read-only one. So it can be completed/obtruded. However, changes to the returned future will not impact this future.
        Specified by:
        toCompletableFuture in interface CompletionStage<T>
